{"title": "Flaying Alive", "content": "We as humans like our skin to be intact. It protects everything inside the body from various diseases, and contains a great quantity of nerve endings \u0097 meaning that to have it forcibly removed is excruciatingly painful, and being stripped of enough of it will lead to a horribly slow death. As a result, flaying is the signature method of Cold-Blooded Torture for some of the very worst of the worst among villains.\n\nScalping is a form of this that was particularly prevalent in Injun Country\u2014 where it was the accepted means of proving a bounty on a Native to a settler government... In real life it was probably more common to take the scalp from a dead foe than from a living one, as their main purpose was to turn in for bounty (more portable than the whole skin.) But there were certainly some documented cases of people surviving a scalping.\n\nFor examples of... reusing the skin see Genuine Human Hide.\n\nAnd if you feel the need for a bit of Soundtrack Dissonance, sing the title to the tune of The Bee Gees' \"Stayin' Alive\".", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlayingAlive?from=Main.FlayedAlive", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ASongOfIceAndFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/TheBeeGees", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/GhostInTheShellStandAloneComplex", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/YuGiOh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SoulEater", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AnatoliaStory", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/ACertainMagicalIndex", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JunjiIto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TokyoGhoul", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DogSoldier", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/MagicTheGathering", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Preacher", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/HackSlash", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/FreddyVsJasonVsAsh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Joker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheJoker", "/pmwiki/pm